Dr. Muhammad Yunus is a Bangladeshi social entrepreneur, economist, and Nobel Peace Prize laureate renowned for his pioneering work in microfinance and social business. Born on June 28, 1940, he founded the Grameen Bank in 1983, introducing the concept of microcreditsmall loans extended to impoverished individuals, especially women, to help them start small businesses and escape poverty.

Key Achievements:

  • Nobel Peace Prize (2006): Awarded jointly to Dr. Yunus and Grameen Bank for their efforts to create economic and social development from below.
  • Grameen Bank Model: Inspired similar microfinance initiatives globally, transforming millions of lives.
  • Social Business Pioneer: Advocated for businesses with a primary goal of addressing social issues rather than maximizing profits.

Education:

  • Earned a Ph.D. in economics from Vanderbilt University, USA.
  • Taught economics at Chittagong University in Bangladesh.

Legacy:

Dr. Yunus's work has been influential in global efforts to combat poverty, particularly through empowering women. Despite controversies and challenges, his innovative approaches to financial inclusion and sustainability continue to inspire development programs worldwide.

Would you like more details about his work or philosophy?

You said:
background size
ChatGPT said:

The background-size property in CSS specifies the size of the background image. Here are common values you can use:

1. cover

Ensures the background image covers the entire container. Some parts of the image may be cropped to maintain its aspect ratio.

css
background-size: cover;

2. contain

Scales the background image to fit entirely within the container. No part of the image is cropped, but it may leave gaps if the container's dimensions don't match the image's aspect ratio.

css
background-size: contain;

3. Specific Dimensions

You can set a specific width and height for the background image.

css
background-size: 100px 200px; /* Width: 100px, Height: 200px */

4. Percentage Values

You can set the size relative to the container's dimensions.

css
background-size: 50% 100%; /* Width: 50% of container, Height: 100% */

5. auto

Keeps the original size of the background image.

css
background-size: auto;

Example:

To use background-size: cover for the .dr_Muhammad_Yunus div:

css
.dr_Muhammad_Yunus {
  background-image: url('your-image-path.jpg');
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
  padding: 20px;
  color: #fff;
}

If you'd like further help with responsive designs or other properties, let me know!

background image margin left
ChatGPT said:

If you want to adjust the background-image position specifically by adding a left margin or offset, you can use the background-position property in CSS.

Adjusting Background Position to Add a Left Margin

You can set the horizontal and vertical positions of the background image using background-position.

Example with Margin Left:

css
.dr_Muhammad_Yunus {
  background-image: url('your-image-path.jpg'); /* Replace with your image URL */
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: 20px center; /* 20px from the left, vertically centered */
  padding: 20px;
  color: #fff;
}

Explanation:

  • 20px center:
    • The 20px moves the background image 20px away from the left edge.
    • The center keeps the image vertically centered.

Alternative: Using background-position with Percentage

You can use percentages to control the left margin more flexibly.

css
background-position: 10% center; /* 10% from the left, vertically centered */

If You Want to Shift the Entire Div:

If the goal is to move the entire div (not just the background image), use the margin-left property instead:

css
.dr_Muhammad_Yunus {
  margin-left: 20px; /* Shifts the entire div */
  background-image: url('your-image-path.jpg');
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
  padding: 20px;
  color: #fff;
}
